from typing import List

class Solution:
    def isArraySpecial(self, nums: List[int]) -> bool:
        for i in range(len(nums) - 1):
            if nums[i] % 2 == nums[i + 1] % 2:
                return False
        return True
```

This code defines a method `isArraySpecial` that checks if the given array `nums` is special according to the problem specification. It iterates through the array and checks the parity of each pair of adjacent elements. If any pair has the same parity, it returns `False`. If all pairs have different parity, it returns `True`.
